---
description: Prefer named constants over magic literals in unit tests
globs: "**/*Test.java,**/test_*.py,**/tests/**/*.py"
alwaysApply: false
---

# Unit test literals

- Extract repeated strings, numeric thresholds, and IDs into `TestConstants` (Java) or a module-level `conftest` / constants module (Python).
- Keep test-specific literals only when they are unique to a single assertion and self-explanatory.
- Reuse production-aligned values (e.g. cold-start average, Redis key prefixes) via constants so tests track domain defaults.
- Prefer `static final` fields and small key-builder methods over inline concatenation in assertions.
